AFRICAN SWINE FEVER - SOUTH AFRICA: (NORTHERN CAPE) DOMESTIC SWINE, OIE
***********************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Wed 30 May 2018
Source: OIE, WAHID [edited]
http://www.oie.int/wahis_2/public/wahid.php/Reviewreport/Review?page_refer=MapFullEventReport&reportid=26719


African swine fever, South Africa
---------------------------------
Information received on [and dated] 30 May 2018 from Dr Bothle Michael Modisane, chief director, Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Animal Production and Health, Pretoria, South Africa

Summary
Report type: immediate notification
Date of start of the event: 23 May 2018
Date of confirmation of the event: 25 May 2018
Reason for notification: recurrence of a listed disease
Date of previous occurrence: 10 Nov 2017
Manifestation of disease: clinical disease
Causal agent: African swine fever [ASF] virus
Nature of diagnosis: clinical, laboratory (advanced), necropsy
This event pertains to a defined zone within the country.

New outbreaks (1)
Total outbreaks: 1
Outbreak 1(ASF_NCP_2018_001): ASF_NCP_2018_001, Nama Khoi, Northern Cape Province
Date of start of the outbreak: 23 May 2018
Outbreak status: continuing (or date resolved not provided)
Epidemiological unit: farm
Total animals affected:
Species / Susceptible / Cases / Deaths / Killed and disposed of / Slaughtered
Swine / 100 / 14 / 14 / 0 / 0

Outbreak statistics [rates apparent, expressed as percentages]
Species / Morbidity rate / Mortality rate / Case fatality rate / Proportion susceptible animals lost*
Swine / 14 / 14 / 100 / 14
*Removed from the susceptible population through death, destruction, and/or slaughter

Epidemiology
Source of the outbreak(s) or origin of infection: unknown or inconclusive
Epidemiological comments: Outbreak outside South Africa's ASF Control Zone. Coordinates modified to protect confidentiality as required by South African Legislation.
Control measures
Measures applied: movement control inside the country; quarantine; vaccination permitted (if a vaccine exists); no treatment of affected animals
Measures to be applied: selective killing and disposal

Diagnostic test results
Laboratory name and type / Species / Test / Test date / Result
Agricultural Research Council-Onderstepoort Veterinary Institute - Transboundary Animals Diseases (OIE reference laboratory) / Swine / polymerase chain reaction (PCR) / 25 May 2018 / Positive

Future reporting
The event is continuing. Weekly follow-up reports will be submitted.

[The location of the outbreak can be seen on the interactive map included in the OIE report at the source URL above.]

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[According to the media release published by the Department of Agriculture, Forestry and Fisheries, Republic of South Africa on 31 May 2018: "An outbreak of African swine fever (ASF) has been reported in the Northern Cape Province in the Springbok area after movement of pigs from the Kimberley area. This falls outside of the ASF controlled areas of the country. The Northern Cape Provincial Veterinary Services are doing follow-up investigations, and control measures are being applied for this outbreak." See more details at https://tinyurl.com/y9sl6scr.

As noted in the comments above, this outbreak occurred outside South Africa's African swine fever control zone, which can be seen on the map at https://tinyurl.com/y86q94kq. - Mod.CRD

HealthMap/ProMED-mail map:
Northern Cape Region, South Africa: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=5830326,12176]
